hackathon-eligibility: You must be enrolled at a college or university institution to attend the Digital Women Code Camp.
hackathon-rules: Your project must be your team's original work, only worked on during the weekend.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: This award focuses on the hack that helps promote diversity and inclusion within the student body, specifically geared toward Goal 4 of the university strategic plan: "Continue to enhance and cultivate the ISU
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Diversity and Inclusion at Iowa State

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Best use of the Arduino or Edison to improve healthcare and well-being.
This award is for the best hack that achieves Digital Women's purpose statement: to support and encourage women.
The best hack that fights evil - like Frozone. Whether it's illiteracy, unclean water, systemic injustice, or the patriarchy, your hack makes peoples' lives better.
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: The Greatest Good You're Ever Gonna Get

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: The stars of Code Camp are the first-time hackathoners who are passionate about learning and growing! This award is for the best hack from a team where Code Camp is their first hackathon.

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=2520 Osborn Dr, Ames, IA 50011, USA
hackathon-description-header: Digital Women Code Camp is a 24-hour hackathon at Iowa State University.
